added.title: Kabooms Part 1
added.description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: The Streak Part 2
added.description: Robin's streak of stopping 52 crimes every year is in jeopardy when members of his team are poached by Kid Flash.

added.title: The Egg
added.description: To impress the mother of Anais' playdate, Nicole forces her family to get classy. Nicole arranges a playdate for Anais with the son of a classy lady she met at the supermarket. She hopes that socializing with the right sort of people will help her children climb Elmore's social ladder. The Wattersons try to impress, but ultimately cannot help revealing their true natures. The grown-ups become convinced they want nothing more to do with each other, just as Anais and her playdate discover how much they have in common.

added.title: The Roots
added.description: When Mom sees Darwin gazing longingly at a fish-tank, she thinks their mammalian lifestyle isn't fulfilling her adopted son and deep down he longs to connect with his fishy roots. So the family try to reconnect him with his aquatic culture. They try fish-food, fish-language and even fish clothes. But when none of it works, they realize they may have to let him go.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The List
added.description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: Know Your Mom
added.description: KO wants to surprise Carol with a gift for Mother's Day, but doesn't know what to get her.

added.title: Glory Days
added.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

added.title: Let's Take a Moment
added.description: Mr. Gar and Carol fight a villain from their past.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: Chili Cook-Off
added.description: Benson wants to get some street cred with the Park Managers' Association and win the big chili cook-off.

added.title: Guys Night 2
added.description: The guys want to give Thomas an epic Guys Night before he goes into hiding forever.

added.title: Eileen Flat Screen
added.description: Rigby wants to set up Eileen's flat screen TV for her.

added.title: Sad Sax
added.description: Mordecai wants to get back together with C.J.

added.title: I See Turtles
added.description: Eileen and the gang want to see baby sea turtles hatch and go into the ocean.

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Kabums Part 1
added.description: Los Titanes están ansiosos por ver la versión cinematográfica de su programa favorito, "Bebés vs. perros", hasta que la presentación de la película hace que se vuelva superaburrida de ver. Para salvarla, los Titanes se meten en la película e interrumpen la charla con mucha acción fascinante.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: La Racha Parte 1
added.description: Llega la temporada de delitos, y Robin está decidido a continuar su racha de impedir 52 delitos por año.

added.title: La Racha Parte 2
added.description: La racha de Robin de impedir 52 delitos por año se pone en peligro cuando los miembros de su equipo se convierten en presas de Kid Flash.

added.title: Gone to His Head
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's new found confidence makes his head big.

added.title: You Can't Handle the Tooth
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus must rescue Pizza Steve from the Tooth Fairy.

added.title: Robo-UG
added.description: Uncle Grandpa builds a robot version of himself to help with his duties.

added.title: Memory of a Memory
added.description: To save Marceline from a sleep spell, Finn and Jake must enter her mind and find the wake spell deep inside her memory.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: The Return of Aunt Grandma
added.description: Aunt Grandma is back and still bent on ruining Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Jake vs. Me-Mow
added.description: Finn and Jake grapple with a tiny feline assassin.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee enlists washed-up TV show host Meteorfire to help him find another of Windblade's psychic shards on Luna-3.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 2
added.description: Bumblebee runs the gauntlet of creepily haunted Luna-3, while Meteorfire records everything on camera for his show.

added.title: Journey to the Valley of Repugnus Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee and Grimlock are separated as they search the depths of Cybertron for another of Windblade's psychic shards, encountering the Monsterbots and the Energon Masters.

added.title: Journey to the Valley of Repugnus Part 2
added.description: Bee and Grimlock navigate the strange cultures of the Energon Masters and Monsterbots, uncovering a shocking secret about the two seemingly-different peoples.

added.title: Wild Wild Wheel Part 2
added.description: WildWheel finds Optimus Prime rebuilding a small Cybertronian town, only to discover the Prime does not recognize him.

added.title: Thunderhowl Part 2
added.description: Released after eons of imprisonment, Thunderhowl helps Bee and Chromia navigate the dangerous Crystal City.

added.title: Thunderhowl Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee and Chromia travel to Crystal City to recover one of Windblade's psychic shards and encounter a long-lost bot.

added.title: Wild Wild Wheel Part 1
added.description: A dangerous lone gunslinger named WildWheel returns to Cybertron looking for Optimus Prime.

added.title: Midnight at the Mayor's Mansion
added.description: When the Mayor's mansion is stalked by a vicious, ghostly monster, he calls the Powerpuff Girls for help.

added.title: The Trouble With Bubbles
added.description: When Bubbles is overworked, she uses her coding skills to come up with a new solution.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Man Up
added.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he to short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: Magnus P.I.
added.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

added.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

added.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
added.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

added.title: The Mysterious Revenger/Wynton vs. Lia
added.description: The Mysterious Revenger: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!/Wynton Vs. Lia: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.
